17:03.787 --> 17:05.334
Andale, Chico!

17:06.580 --> 17:08.174
Come on, Jets!

17:08.916 --> 17:10.260
Hey, Jets!

17:11.044 --> 17:12.215
Hello!

17:15.882 --> 17:17.555
Jets, come on! Julio!

17:18.009 --> 17:19.477
Come on!

17:22.137 --> 17:23.685
Jets!

17:28.560 --> 17:30.188
Come on, boys!

17:31.564 --> 17:33.032
Come on, now!

18:19.529 --> 18:20.781
Jets!

18:55.356 --> 18:59.577
Break it up, you punks! Cut it out!
Come on, guys! Break it up, I said!

18:59.652 --> 19:01.905
Come on, break it up! Come on!

19:01.988 --> 19:04.832
How many times have I told you
punks to cut this stuff out?

19:04.908 --> 19:09.004
- Why, if it ain't Lt. Schrank!
- Top of the day, Lt. Schrank.

19:09.078 --> 19:12.582
- And Officer Krupke.
- Top of the day, Officer Krupke.

19:12.665 --> 19:15.509
- I'll give you the top of the head.
- Hey you, get down!

19:15.627 --> 19:18.506
- But we're having such fun.
- We enjoy the playground.

19:18.588 --> 19:21.512
See, it keeps us deprived children
off of the foul city streets.

19:21.591 --> 19:22.638
Shut up!

19:22.717 --> 19:24.560
And born like we was
on the hot pavement.

19:24.636 --> 19:27.435
- You wanna get your skull broke?
- Hey, Baby John, come here!

19:28.181 --> 19:29.353
Come here!

19:33.895 --> 19:35.238
All right!

19:35.355 --> 19:37.824
Now, which one of these
Puerto Ricans bloodied you?

19:39.484 --> 19:41.361
- Sir...
- Which one?

19:41.819 --> 19:43.366
Excuse me, sir.

19:43.613 --> 19:45.365
As a matter of fact...

19:45.698 --> 19:48.702
we suspicion that the
job was done by a cop.

19:49.243 --> 19:50.620
- Two cops.
- At the very least.

19:50.703 --> 19:51.670
Impossible.

19:51.746 --> 19:54.590
In America, nothing is impossible.

19:55.583 --> 19:57.381
All right, wise guys...

19:58.044 --> 19:59.637
now, you listen to me!

19:59.712 --> 20:01.055
All of you!

20:01.631 --> 20:03.725
You hoodlums don't own these streets.

20:03.800 --> 20:07.304
And I've had all the roughhouse I'm
gonna put up with around here!

20:07.387 --> 20:11.984
You wanna kill each other, kill each other!
But you ain't gonna do it on my beat!

20:12.058 --> 20:14.060
- Are there any questions?
- Yes, sir.

20:14.894 --> 20:17.397
Would you mind translating
that into Spanish?

20:19.524 --> 20:23.028
Get your friends out of here, Bernardo.

20:23.903 --> 20:25.405
And stay out!

20:30.910 --> 20:32.127
Please.

20:34.414 --> 20:35.882
Okay, Sharks.

20:37.417 --> 20:38.634
Vámonos.

20:48.094 --> 20:49.596
Boy, oh boy!

20:49.762 --> 20:52.732
As if this neighborhood
wasn't crummy enough!

20:55.101 --> 20:57.103
Now, look, fellas. Fellas!

20:57.395 --> 20:59.272
Look, let's be reasonable...

20:59.355 --> 21:01.904
if I don't get a little law
and order around here...

21:01.983 --> 21:04.577
I get busted down to
a traffic corner...

21:04.652 --> 21:07.121
and your friend don't
like traffic corners.

21:07.196 --> 21:09.164
So, that means you're gonna
start makin' nice...

21:09.240 --> 21:11.242
with the PR's from now on.

21:12.910 --> 21:14.662
I said nice! Get it?

21:15.747 --> 21:17.465
'Cause if you don't...

21:17.540 --> 21:21.465
and I catch any of you doin' any
more brawlin' in my territory...

21:21.544 --> 21:24.218
I'm gonna personally beat the livin'
crud out of each and every one of you...

21:24.297 --> 21:27.016
and see that you go to
the can and rot there!

21:30.344 --> 21:34.269
- Say good-bye to the nice boys, Krupke.
- Good-bye, boys.

21:38.811 --> 21:40.438
"Good-bye, boys."

21:41.439 --> 21:42.816
Jail? Gee.

21:43.691 --> 21:45.568
"You hoodlums don't own the streets."

21:45.651 --> 21:48.074
Go play in the park.
Keep off of the grass.

21:48.154 --> 21:50.156
- Get out of the house!
- Keep off the block.

21:50.239 --> 21:51.991
- Get outta here.
- Keep off the world!

21:52.075 --> 21:54.419
A gang that don't own
the street is nothin'!

21:54.494 --> 21:55.996
We do own it!

21:57.580 --> 21:59.457
Come on, Jets, round out!

21:59.999 --> 22:04.049
- Not you, Anybodys! Beat it!
- Riff, you gotta let me in the gang!

22:04.128 --> 22:07.803
Didn't you just see me? I was smash!
I'm a killer, I wanna fight.

22:07.882 --> 22:10.101
How else she gonna get
a guy to touch her?

22:10.176 --> 22:13.430
- You dirty rat!
- Come on, the road, little girl! The road!

22:13.554 --> 22:14.806
Beat it!

22:16.682 --> 22:18.901
- Beat it!
- Okay, come on.

22:25.483 --> 22:27.030
Okay, now listen!

22:27.110 --> 22:30.410
Now, we fought hard for this turf,
and we ain't just gonna give it up.

22:30.488 --> 22:32.411
The Emeralds claimed
it, we shot 'em out.

22:32.490 --> 22:35.494
The Hawks, remember? They tried to take
it away, we knocked them down the cellar.

22:35.576 --> 22:38.705
- But these PR's are different.
- They multiply. Like cockroaches.

22:38.788 --> 22:40.756
- Shut the door!
- They're eatin' all the food.

22:40.832 --> 22:43.460
- Breathin' all the air.
- Help! I'm drowning in tamale.

22:43.543 --> 22:46.092
And you heard what that Lt. Schrank said...

22:46.170 --> 22:49.515
we gotta make nice with
them Puerto Ricans or else.

22:49.590 --> 22:51.809
We gotta let 'em move in
right under our noses...

22:51.884 --> 22:53.978
- and take it all away from us or else.
- No!

22:54.053 --> 22:55.896
You're damn right, no!

22:56.222 --> 23:00.352
So what're we gonna do, buddy boys?
I'll tell you what we're gonna do.

23:00.434 --> 23:02.061
We're gonna speed back!

23:02.228 --> 23:05.607
We're gonna move like lightnin', and
we're gonna clean them Sharks up...

23:05.690 --> 23:06.907
once and for all.

23:06.983 --> 23:09.782
So they ain't never gonna
set foot on our turf again!

23:10.778 --> 23:14.453
We're gonna do it in one all-out fight.

23:14.574 --> 23:17.703
- A rumble! Chop, chop!
- Now cool, Action Boy.

23:17.910 --> 23:22.632
The Sharks want a piece of this world, too.
And they're real down boys.

23:23.082 --> 23:24.959
They might ask for blades...

23:25.418 --> 23:27.341
- zip guns.
- Zip guns?

23:29.255 --> 23:32.680
I ain't finalizin' and
sayin' they will, Baby John.

23:32.758 --> 23:36.979
I'm just sayin' that they might,
and we gotta be prepared.

23:38.181 --> 23:40.024
Now, what's your mood, Jets?

23:40.099 --> 23:42.773
- I say go, go!
- I say mix!

23:42.852 --> 23:44.149
- I say sock 'em!
- Tear them!

23:44.228 --> 23:48.904
- Yeah, but if they say blades or guns...
- I say let's just forget the whole thing.

23:48.983 --> 23:51.202
- What?
- What do you say, Riff?

23:52.403 --> 23:56.624
I say this turf is small,
but it's all we got.

23:57.700 --> 24:00.954
I wanna hold it like we
always held it, with skin!

24:02.580 --> 24:05.333
But if they say blades, I say blades.

24:05.917 --> 24:08.511
If they say guns, I say guns.

24:09.378 --> 24:12.302
I say I want the Jets
to be the number one!

24:12.423 --> 24:16.348
- To sail! To hold the sky!
- Then rev us off! Voom va-voom!

24:18.221 --> 24:19.393
Okay, cats, we rumble!

24:19.889 --> 24:21.141
Now...

24:21.682 --> 24:23.525
protocality calls for a war council...

24:23.601 --> 24:26.104
between us and the Sharks
to set the whole thing up.

24:26.187 --> 24:29.031
So I will personally give
the bad news to Bernardo.

24:29.106 --> 24:31.325
- You gotta take a lieutenant with you.
- That's me.

24:31.400 --> 24:33.073
- That's Tony.
- Who needs Tony?

24:33.152 --> 24:34.699
We need Tony!

24:35.029 --> 24:37.532
He's got a rep that's bigger
than the whole West Side!

24:37.615 --> 24:40.710
- He don't belong no more.
- Now, cut it, Action!

24:40.952 --> 24:44.047
- Me and Tony started the Jets.
- So where is he?

24:44.163 --> 24:47.633
- How come he takes a lousy, stinkin' job?
- Youth Board corrupted him.

24:47.708 --> 24:49.756
- Yeah, temporary sickness!
- Wait and see.

24:49.835 --> 24:52.429
Remember them fists the day
we clobbered the Emeralds?

24:52.505 --> 24:55.349
- He saved my ever-loving neck!
- Sure! He'll do it again, too!

24:55.424 --> 24:58.598
He always came through for
us and he always will.

24:58.678 --> 25:01.431
♪ When you're a Jet
you're a Jet all the way ♪

25:01.514 --> 25:04.984
♪ From your first cigarette
to your last dyin' day ♪

25:05.059 --> 25:07.812
♪ When you're a Jet
let 'em do what they can ♪

25:07.895 --> 25:09.522
♪ You've got brothers around ♪

25:09.605 --> 25:11.448
♪ You're a family man ♪

25:11.524 --> 25:12.946
♪ You're never alone ♪

25:13.025 --> 25:15.073
♪ You're never disconnected ♪

25:15.695 --> 25:17.368
♪ You're home with your own ♪

25:17.530 --> 25:18.952
♪ When company's expected ♪

25:19.031 --> 25:20.658
♪ You're well-protected ♪

25:20.741 --> 25:23.620
♪ Then you are set with a capital 'J' ♪

25:23.703 --> 25:26.673
♪ Which you'll never forget
till they cart you away ♪

25:26.747 --> 25:27.964
♪ When you're a Jet ♪

25:28.040 --> 25:30.338
♪ You stay a ♪

25:30.501 --> 25:32.299
♪ Jet ♪

25:35.548 --> 25:38.802
Now, I know Tony like I know me, and
I guarantee you can count him in.

25:38.884 --> 25:41.353
- Let's get crackin'.
- Where will you find Bernardo?

25:41.429 --> 25:44.603
- It ain't safe in PR territory.
- He'll be at tonight's gym dance.

25:44.682 --> 25:47.856
- But the gym's neutral territory.
- A-Rab, I'm gonna make nice with him.

25:47.935 --> 25:50.358
- I'm only gonna challenge him.
- Right, daddy-o.

25:50.438 --> 25:53.362
So listen, everybody dress
up sweet and sharp.

25:53.441 --> 25:56.490
Meet Tony and me at the dance
after 10:00, and walk tall!

25:56.569 --> 25:58.663
- We always walk tall!
- We're Jets!

25:58.738 --> 25:59.910
The greatest!

26:00.114 --> 26:01.240
♪ When you're a Jet ♪

26:01.324 --> 26:02.826
♪ You're the top cat in town ♪

26:02.908 --> 26:04.410
♪ You're the gold-medal kid ♪

26:04.493 --> 26:06.495
♪ With the heavyweight crown ♪

26:06.579 --> 26:07.751
♪ When you're a Jet ♪

26:07.830 --> 26:09.332
♪ You're the swinginest thing ♪

26:09.415 --> 26:10.962
♪ Little boy you're a man ♪

26:11.042 --> 26:12.794
♪ Little man, you're a king ♪

26:12.877 --> 26:14.345
♪ The Jets are in gear ♪

26:14.420 --> 26:16.343
♪ Our cylinders are clickin' ♪

26:17.131 --> 26:18.428
♪ The Sharks'll steer clear ♪

26:18.507 --> 26:21.852
♪ 'Cause every Puerto Rican's
a lousy chicken ♪

26:21.927 --> 26:23.053
♪ Here come the Jets ♪

26:23.137 --> 26:24.559
♪ Like a bat out of hell ♪

26:24.638 --> 26:26.140
♪ Someone gets in our way ♪

26:26.223 --> 26:27.941
♪ Someone don't feel so well ♪

26:28.017 --> 26:29.189
♪ Here come the Jets ♪

26:29.268 --> 26:30.736
♪ Little world, step aside ♪

26:30.811 --> 26:32.358
♪ Better go underground ♪

26:32.438 --> 26:34.031
♪ Better run, better hide ♪

26:34.106 --> 26:35.779
♪ We're drawin' the line ♪

26:35.858 --> 26:37.451
♪ So keep your noses hidden ♪

26:38.110 --> 26:39.532
♪ We're hangin' a sign ♪

26:39.612 --> 26:41.034
♪ Says 'visitors forbidden' ♪

26:41.113 --> 26:42.786
♪ And we ain't kiddin' ♪

26:42.948 --> 26:44.370
♪ Here come the Jets, yeah ♪

26:44.450 --> 26:45.747
♪ And we're gonna beat ♪

26:45.826 --> 26:47.203
♪ Every last buggin' gang ♪

26:47.286 --> 26:48.754
♪ On the whole buggin' street ♪

26:48.829 --> 26:50.831
♪ On the whole buggin' ♪

26:50.915 --> 26:52.462
♪ Ever-lovin' ♪

26:52.541 --> 26:54.839
♪ Street ♪

26:57.755 --> 26:58.847
Yeah!

26:59.215 --> 27:02.435
- Tony, you're not even listenin'.
- I read you loud and clear, Riff.

27:02.510 --> 27:05.730
- Then why don't you say somethin'?
- I don't wanna hurt your feelings.

27:05.805 --> 27:08.900
- You're my buddy, my pal, my best friend!
- Womb to tomb?

27:10.059 --> 27:11.481
Birth to earth.

27:11.560 --> 27:15.155
That's why you gotta come to the
dance tonight and stand up with me.

27:15.439 --> 27:17.658
Come on, Tony. Just say yes.

27:17.817 --> 27:20.570
Riff, did you ever stop to figure...

27:20.653 --> 27:23.748
how many bubbles there are in one
bottle of this here soda pop?

27:23.823 --> 27:25.621
Tony, this is important!

27:25.699 --> 27:27.918
Everything's important, Riff...

27:28.160 --> 27:30.709
you, me, the sweet guy I work for.

27:31.455 --> 27:33.674
The Sharks walk bad. They bite hard.

27:33.958 --> 27:36.962
- And if we don't stop them now...
- Here! Work for a living.

27:37.753 --> 27:41.883
How do you like that? Four and a half
years I live with a buddy and his family.

27:41.966 --> 27:44.014
I think I'm diggin' a guy's character.

27:45.302 --> 27:48.146
Boy, am I a victim of
disappointment in you!

27:49.056 --> 27:51.024
End your sufferin', little man.

27:51.100 --> 27:53.694
Why don't you just pack up
your gear and move out?

27:53.769 --> 27:55.487
'Cause your ma's hot for me.

27:59.024 --> 28:02.369
No! It's 'cause I hate livin'
with my buggin' uncle!

28:02.445 --> 28:04.698
- Come on!
- Come on, uncle!

28:06.365 --> 28:07.366
Now...

28:08.075 --> 28:09.873
go play games with the Jets.

28:10.077 --> 28:12.079
And why not? They're the greatest.

28:12.538 --> 28:13.710
Ain't they?

28:14.206 --> 28:15.332
Were.

28:17.877 --> 28:19.595
You found somethin' better?

28:20.171 --> 28:22.390
No. Not yet, but...

28:23.757 --> 28:25.054
But What?

28:26.385 --> 28:28.308
You won't dig it, Riff.

28:28.804 --> 28:30.147
So try me.

28:31.182 --> 28:33.059
Come on, Tony, try me.

28:36.937 --> 28:38.029
Okay.

28:41.609 --> 28:44.909
Every single night for the
last month, I wake up...

28:45.821 --> 28:47.573
and I'm reaching out.

28:49.200 --> 28:51.453
- For what?
- I don't know.

28:52.578 --> 28:53.795
A dame?

28:54.914 --> 28:58.168
It's right outside the door,
just around the corner...

28:58.542 --> 29:00.010
but it's comin'.

29:00.085 --> 29:01.302
What is?

29:02.129 --> 29:03.597
I don't know. It...

29:05.090 --> 29:07.718
it's like the kick I used
to get from bein' a Jet.

29:07.801 --> 29:09.553
Now you're talkin'!

29:09.637 --> 29:11.981
Man, without a gang, you're an orphan.

29:12.056 --> 29:14.650
With a gang, you walk in
twos, threes, fours...

29:14.725 --> 29:16.022
and your crew is the best...

29:16.101 --> 29:18.775
when you're a Jet, you're out
in the sun, buddy boy...

29:18.854 --> 29:20.026
you're home free home!

29:20.105 --> 29:21.857
Riff, I've had it!

29:25.194 --> 29:26.411
Tony...

29:27.905 --> 29:29.282
Tony, look at me, will ya?

29:29.365 --> 29:31.367
- Come on, look at me.
- I'm lookin' at you.

29:31.450 --> 29:35.296
Now, I never asked the time
of day from a clock, did I?

29:36.372 --> 29:40.252
I never asked nothin' from
nobody, but I'm askin' you...

29:40.543 --> 29:42.170
come to the dance tonight.

29:43.462 --> 29:45.556
I promised Doc I'd clean
up the store tonight.

29:45.631 --> 29:47.633
Then do it after the dance.

29:48.467 --> 29:51.391
Tony, I already told the
guys you'd be there.

29:51.679 --> 29:54.398
If you don't show,
I'll be marked lousy.

29:55.849 --> 29:57.192
What time'd you tell 'em?

29:57.518 --> 29:58.690
10:00.

29:59.311 --> 30:01.188
For me, Tony, for Riff!

30:05.234 --> 30:07.077
- 10:00 it is.
- Womb to tomb?

30:07.152 --> 30:09.200
Birth to earth, and I'll
live to regret this.

30:09.280 --> 30:12.625
Who knows? Maybe what you're waitin'
for'll be twitchin' at the dance tonight.

30:12.700 --> 30:14.327
Yeah. Who knows?

30:20.332 --> 30:21.675
Who knows?

30:24.336 --> 30:26.839
♪ Could be ♪

30:27.715 --> 30:30.514
♪ Who knows? ♪

30:30.843 --> 30:32.811
♪ There's somethin' due any day ♪

30:32.886 --> 30:34.433
♪ I will know right away ♪

30:34.513 --> 30:37.232
♪ Soon as it shows ♪

30:37.600 --> 30:39.819
♪ It may come cannonballin'
down through the sky ♪

30:39.893 --> 30:43.022
♪ Gleam in its eye, bright as a rose ♪

30:43.981 --> 30:46.609
♪ Who knows? ♪

30:47.192 --> 30:49.286
♪ It's only just out of reach ♪

30:49.361 --> 30:50.863
♪ Down the block, on a beach ♪

30:50.946 --> 30:53.574
♪ Under a tree ♪

30:54.283 --> 30:56.126
♪ I got a feelin' there's a miracle due ♪

30:56.201 --> 30:59.045
♪ Gonna come true, comin' to me ♪

31:02.333 --> 31:03.801
♪ Could it be? ♪

31:03.876 --> 31:05.128
♪ Yes, it could ♪

31:05.210 --> 31:07.633
♪ Something's comin', somethin' good ♪

31:07.713 --> 31:09.841
♪ If I can wait ♪

31:10.132 --> 31:11.475
♪ Something's comin' ♪

31:11.550 --> 31:13.427
♪ I don't know what it is ♪

31:13.510 --> 31:17.014
♪ But it is gonna be great ♪

31:17.681 --> 31:18.898
♪ With a click ♪

31:18.974 --> 31:20.146
♪ With a shock ♪

31:20.225 --> 31:22.728
♪ Phone'll jingle, door'll knock ♪

31:22.811 --> 31:25.030
♪ Open the latch ♪

31:25.189 --> 31:27.533
♪ Somethin's comin', don't know when ♪

31:27.608 --> 31:29.485
♪ But it's soon, catch the moon ♪

31:29.568 --> 31:31.912
♪ One-handed catch ♪

31:32.488 --> 31:36.413
♪ Around the corner ♪

31:37.493 --> 31:41.418
♪ Or whistlin' down the river ♪

31:43.082 --> 31:46.882
♪ Come on, deliver ♪

31:48.003 --> 31:49.880
♪ To me ♪

31:53.759 --> 31:54.976
♪ Will it be? ♪

31:55.052 --> 31:56.269
♪ Yes, it will ♪

31:56.345 --> 31:58.894
♪ Maybe just by holdin' still ♪

31:58.972 --> 32:01.145
♪ It'll be there ♪

32:01.517 --> 32:03.770
♪ Come on, somethin', come on in ♪

32:03.852 --> 32:05.695
♪ Don't be shy meet a guy ♪

32:05.771 --> 32:08.115
♪ Pull up a chair ♪

32:08.774 --> 32:13.075
♪ The air is hummin' ♪

32:13.946 --> 32:17.951
♪ And somethin' great is comin' ♪

32:20.160 --> 32:22.663
♪ Who knows? ♪

32:23.455 --> 32:25.549
♪ It's only just out of reach ♪

